U.K. Financial Services Authority
Chief Executive Officer  Hector Sants  said the new regulator
being set up to take over the supervision of large U.K.
financial institutions in 2013, the  Prudential Regulatory
Authority , should be given the power to investigate bank
failures and publish its findings, the Financial Times reported,
citing an interview.  To contact the reporter on this story:
